Indicates if the billing, shipping, payment, tax, and currency information on the order should be defaulted from the customer information. When the flag is set to "Y", and a valid customer is found, the billing, shipping, and tax information on the order will be defaulted either from the customer or from the customer contact. This flag determines whether an hold has been placed on the order when certain hold types criteria are met. If order is on hold, default configuration will stop the shceduling and release process for the order. The flag is reset to 'N' when all the hold types have been resolved on the order and all of its order lines. Based on hold type configuration, certain transactions may not be allowed to process. Note that there is no validation made on the hold applied but this flag can be reset by the application based on hold types existed on the order.
Default:
N
Valid Values:
Y
or
N

Attribute.Name: ItemTrackingLevel
Attribute.Description: This value is equal to 40. This attribute is present in Statuses greater or equal to Created status and less than or equal to Released Status in case of PICK. In case of SHP this atribute will be present in statuses greater than or equal to Scheduled status and less than or equal to Released Status. If there are OrderStatuses element for which ExpectedShipmentDate and ExpectedDeliveryDate is same and satisfying the statuses that are mentioned above then this attribute is present only in one OrderStatus element. This attribute will be present only when the TrackingLevel in the OrderLine element has value as 40.
